This paper deals with the optimization of signal processing in Cloud Radio Access Networks (C-RANs), which are wireless cellular networks that rely on centralized processing and cloud-based infrastructure. The paper proposes a dynamic nested clustering algorithm to improve the scalability of baseband-processing and channel-estimation complexity, which are key challenges in large-scale C-RANs. This work involves aspects of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and architecture (cs.AR).
